cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper is about a theorem prover that operates on a sequent calculus formulation of first-order logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper uses Standard ML as the programming language for the implementation of the prover. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of logical inference and unification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as theorem proving is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with formal logic and the implementation of a formal system.
